{
  "stem": "14060.9",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And the least, I must say, had to say the rabbis, because they also had no answer to it, particularly the ones who went through the camp.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And I must say a thing of the-- one of the extreme Hasidic movements today of America, the Satmars, who are many points very extreme.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And the Satmar also in Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And afterwards, he got to Switzerland, because he was taken out with that Kastmer transport.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And I'm not a Satmar.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "Of course, I'm not [INAUDIBLE] at all with a perfectly legitimate Ashkenazim and not Hasidim.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "Said that anybody who went through the camps, and the Holocaust generally, and doesn't keep anything, he has got no question to ask him.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "He can't say anything to him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "Now, that is a great statement, I think.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And basically I think till this day, whoever touches that subject from a religious point of view is getting himself into hot water and trouble.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "Because with our normal thinking, it's difficult to fathom and place it in the right context.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "You can blame it on anybody.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "The fact is, it happened.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Ah, now that is interesting to say.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I have a very secularly modern, but a strictly Orthodox upbringing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so has all my family, all around.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when I came back and I met my uncle, my mother's brothers, who were the same style of religion and remained so, one of the first questions my uncle asked me, are you still religious?",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, you can deduct from-- deduce from that that even in his mind it was obvious that after what happened it could have very easily been that I wasn't.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
